Definition: seize and take control without authority and possibly with force
Example: take as one's right or possession; He assumed to himself the right to fill all positions in the town; he usurped my rights; She seized control of the throne after her husband died
Synonyms: noun, act, assumption, usurp, usurpation, person, usurper, seize, take_over, takeover, arrogate, arrogation, arrogator, take, and, control, without, authority, possibly, with, force, as, one, s, right, or, possession, He, assumed, to, himself, the, fill, all, positions, in, town, he, usurped, my, rights, She, seized, of, throne, after, her, husband, died
Frame: 8
Category: verb.possession
